item.title: Private sector hiring in US cools more than expected: ADP
item.description: Job gains in the US private sector slowed again in May on a slump in manufacturing, payroll firm ADP said Wednesday, in a further sign the world's largest economy could be cooling. Employers added 152,000 jobs last month, down from a revised 188,000 figure in April and less than analysts anticipated, the report said. This was due to a steep decline in manufacturing, added ADP, noting that leisure and hospitality also showed softer job growth.

item.title: What is the importance of balance in an art composition?
item.description: Artists generally strive to create artwork that is balanced.
